markets.question: Will Kamala lead by 1.5-1.9 August 30?
markets.description:
This is a market on the RCP Polling Average margin between Donald Trump and Kamala Harris as of August 30, 2024, 12:00 PM ET. The spread referenced in the first table on the "2024 General Election: Trump vs. Harris" page at https://www.realclearpolling.com/polls/president/general/2024/trump-vs-harris will be used to resolve this market.

This market will resolve to 'Yes' if the RCP Polling Average margin is between Harris +1.5 (inclusive) and Harris +1.9 (inclusive) percentage points. Otherwise, this market will resolve to 'No'.

The RCP Polling Average will be checked on August 30, 12:00 PM ET.

Please note, this market refers specifically to the margin for RCP polling average as presented in the aforementioned chart in the column titled 'Spread'. This includes any adjustments or methodology changes made by RCP in their calculation of the polling average or the date range used.

If the RCP Polling Average margin data between Kamala Harris and Donald Trump is not available by September 3, 2024, 11:59 PM ET, another credible source of polling data as of August 30, 12:00 PM ET will be used for market resolution.

markets.question: Trump mentioned between 60 and 79 times at the DNC on day 4?
markets.description:
This market refers to anything said in person on the main stage of the United Center on the fourth night of the DNC. Programming is currently scheduled to begin at 5:30 PM CT and end at 10:15 PM CT (see: https://demconvention.com/schedule/). 

This market will resolve to "Yes" if "Trump" is said between 60 (inclusive) and 79 (inclusive) times on the fourth night of the DNC.  Otherwise, the market will resolve to "No".

Any live mention on the main stage which is audible on the stream of the event will count toward this market. Ads won't count - only in-person mentions count. Pluralization/possessive of "Trump" will count toward the resolution of this market, however other forms will NOT count. Note for example if "Donald is running for President" is said, it doesn't count as a mention - only "Trump" counts.

Compound words will count as long as "Trump" is part of the compound word and references the meaning which refers to the person Donald Trump.

The resolution source will be the video of the fourth night of the DNC.
